                <%= link_to "View products", @technologies[1], :class=>"btn btn-primary text-right" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
          <div class="container">

          <div class="row tech-pictures">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <%=image_tag("crystalcool/crystalcool-exploded.png", :class=>"img-responsive")%>
            </div>

          </div>


          <div class="row tech-header">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <h3 class="flat-font"><%= "Aurora's groundbreaking CrystalCool™ technology is literally the coolest thing to hit the LED market" %></h3>
              <h4 class="flat-font"><%= "CrystalCool™ uses nanotechnology to provide extremely effective heat dissipation and thermal management." %></h4>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-content">
            <div class="col-md-12">
               <p>LEDs generate significant amounts of heat in order to produce light. This normally requires a large thermal heatsink to adequately cool an LED lamp. The higher the lumen output, the more LEDs required, the larger the heatsink.</p>

               <p>Heat directly affects an LED lamp's quality of light over time. Without adequately channeling the heat away from the lamp's temperature sensitive electronics, colour temperature can shift and lumen output depreciation accelerates. Clearly, LED lamp reliability and longevity depends on its thermal management.</p>

              
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-pictures">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <figure>
                <%=image_tag("crystalcool/4d-ceramic-nanolayers.jpg", :class=>"img-responsive")%>
                <figcaption>Heat is conducted away from the LED chip and Aluminum MCPCB (1) by CrystalCool™'s specially designed nano-layering structure (2) and nano carbon layer (3).</figcaption>
              </figure>  
            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="row tech-header">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <h3 class="flat-font"><%= "CrystalCool™ nano layers" %></h3>
            </div>
          </div>

           <div class="row tech-content">
            <div class="col-md-12">
               <p>With CrystalCool™ technology, 150 layers of decreasingly dense, 4D ceramic nano material conduct heat away from the lamp's temperature-sensitive electronic components.</p>

               <p>The layers form a 3D surface upon the aluminium metal core printed circuit board, or MCPCB. The 4th dimension is time as heat produced by the LED travels through the layers, enabling increasingly rapid dissipation as the nano material becomes less dense. One effect is a 10 percent reduction in temperature at the solder point, which enables increased reliability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-pictures">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <figure>
                <%=image_tag("crystalcool/graphic-regmcpcb-vs-crystalcool-horiz.png", :class=>"img-responsive")%>
                <figcaption>Regular MCPCB vs 4D CrystalCool™ </figcaption>
              </figure>  
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-header">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <h3 class="flat-font"><%= "Higher quality, brighter light for longer" %></h3>
            </div>
          </div>

           <div class="row tech-content">
            <div class="col-md-12">
               <p>Such efficient thermal management allows for an ultra high lumen output and and lifetime, meaning lamps can now produce a higher quality of light, for longer.</p>

               <p>Additionally, CrystalCool™ dramatically slows the rate of lumen depreciation. Relying solely conventional heatsinking will help with the gradual fading of LED light, but, as the graph shows, it still diminishes at a much faster rate when compared to CrystalCool™ thermal management. </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-pictures">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <figure>
                <%=image_tag("crystalcool/graphic-crystalcool-longerlife.png", :class=>"img-responsive")%>
                <figcaption>CrystalCool™ Longerlife</figcaption>
              </figure>  
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row tech-header">
            <div class="col-md-12 centralize">
              <h3 class="flat-font"><%= "Optimised fire rated lamps and luminaires" %></h3>
            </div>
          </div>

           <div class="row tech-content">
            <div class="col-md-12">
               <p>We feature our CrystalCool™ technology inside our line of Firetec™ lamps and in select fire rated downlights. Firetec™ lamps are the only lamps optimised for use in fire rated, enclosed or semi-enclosed luminaires where thermal management is crucial.</p>

               <p>Our Firetec™ lamps are fully dimmable and have a high colour rendering index of 80. These brilliant lamps have an average lifespan of 25,000 hours to 70 percent lumen maintenance and come with a 3 year warranty. Increase it to 5 years when you pair Firetec lamps with Universal fire rated downlights for the ultimate combination of maximum lamp life and performance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>


        </div><!-- container -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

